body:

[Creative Commons' wiki](http://wiki.creativecommons.org) is now an [OpenID](http://openid.net/) enabled-site. Don't hesitate - if you don't have one yet - to create an OpenID account. There are severals [OpenID providers](http://openid.net/wiki/index.php/OpenIDServers) so merely choose one from the list below :

• [MyOpenID](http://www.myopenid.com/)  
• [VIdentity](https://getopenid.com/)  
• [GetOpenID](https://getopenid.com/)  
• [TypeKey](http://www.typekey.com/t/typekey)  
• [MyLID](http://pip.verisignlabs.com/)  
• [VeriSign Personnal Identity Provider](http://pip.verisignlabs.com/)

A really nice screencast by [Don McAllister](http://blog.screencastsonline.com/scoblog) explaining how to use OpenID can be viewed [here](http://screencastsonline.com/sco/Shows/files/SCO0107-openid.html).

Edit: Another [screencast](http://simonwillison.net/2006/openid-screencast/) from Simon Willison

